# Genius Gateway - Multi-License Structure

The Genius Gateway project uses different licenses for different components to best serve the open source hardware and software communities while protecting the work done in reverse engineering.

## License Summary

| Component | License | Files | Rationale |
|-----------|---------|-------|-----------|
| **Hardware** | CC BY-SA 4.0 | `cae/*`, hardware docs | Open hardware standard with ShareAlike |
| **Backend Software** | GPL v3 | `src/*`, `lib/*`, firmware | Strong copyleft for reverse engineering work |
| **Frontend Software** | MIT | `interface/*`, web assets | Permissive for UI customization |
| **Documentation** | CC BY 4.0 | `docs/*`, `README.md` | Attribution-only for documentation |

---

## Hardware License: Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-SA 4.0)

**Applies to:** PCB designs, schematics, CAD files, mechanical drawings, hardware documentation

**Files:** `cae/*`, hardware-related documentation in `docs/hardware/*`

**License URL:** https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

**Summary:** You are free to share and adapt the hardware designs, even commercially, as long as you provide attribution and distribute derivatives under the same license.

**Attribution:** "Genius Gateway Hardware Design by hmbacher (https://github.com/hmbacher/genius-gateway) is licensed under CC BY-SA 4.0"

---

## Backend Software License: GNU General Public License v3 (GPL v3)

**Applies to:** ESP32 firmware, protocol implementation, reverse engineering code, backend services

**Files:** `src/*`, `lib/*`, `platformio.ini`, build scripts related to firmware

Copyright (C) 2024 hmbacher

This program is free software: you can redistribute it and/or modify
it under the terms of the GNU General Public License as published by
the Free Software Foundation, either version 3 of the License, or
(at your option) any later version.

This program is distributed in the hope that it will be useful,
but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of
MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.  See the
GNU General Public License for more details.

You should have received a copy of the GNU General Public License
along with this program.  If not, see <https://www.gnu.org/licenses/>.

**Rationale:** The GPL v3 ensures that improvements to the reverse-engineered protocol implementation and firmware remain open source, preventing proprietary derivatives while allowing commercial use.

---

